ABSTRACT
A sensor, such as a motion sensor and/or an occupancy
sensor, can include the capability of communicating wire-
lessly with a user device such that sensor settings can be
adjusted via an application running on the user device. The
sensor settings may determine when one or more light
sources (e.g., a light fixture, a light bulb, a light emitting
diode (LED), etc.) turn on and/or the amount of light
produced by the one or more light sources.
